com.googlecode.cqengine.index.navigable

Class NavigableIndex.IndexRangeLookupFunction<O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.cqengine.index.navigable.NavigableIndex.IndexRangeLookupFunction<O>
  • Type Parameters:
    O - The type of object stored in the result sets
    Enclosing class:
    NavigableIndex<A extends Comparable<A>,O>

    protected abstract class NavigableIndex.IndexRangeLookupFunction<O>
extends Object
    An interface which when implemented encapsulates the logic to retrieve zero or more ResultSets from an index, where the logic for selecting these ResultSets is implemented by the perform() method.

    • Constructor Detail

      • NavigableIndex.IndexRangeLookupFunction

        protected NavigableIndex.IndexRangeLookupFunction(Query<O> query,
                                       boolean filterFirstResultSet,
                                       boolean filterLastResultSet)
        The following arguments are useful when the index uses a Quantizer, and so the stored sets of objects might need to be filtered on retrieval.
        Parameters:
        query - The query against which objects should be filtered
        filterFirstResultSet - True if the first StoredResultSet returned by the function should be filtered to return only objects which actually match the query - typically true for GreaterThan and Between queries and false for LessThan queries
        filterLastResultSet - True if the last StoredResultSet returned by the function should be filtered to return only objects which actually match the query - typically true for LessThan and Between queries and false for GreaterThan queries
